
# Kangalert – Wildlife Strike Reporter 🦘

**Kangalert** is a mobile-friendly web app that allows road users to quickly report wildlife strikes (e.g. kangaroos, wombats, possums) and notify local rescue services. It helps reduce duplicate reports, improve response times, and build a clearer picture of wildlife strike hotspots.

> 🔄 This is the **public version** of Kangalert. For rescue teams and volunteers, please use the https://kangalert-rescuer.streamlit.app.

---

## 🚗 Features for Road Users

- 📍 Automatically detects your location and centres the map
- 📝 Submit wildlife strike reports with condition, joey presence, and optional photo
- 🗺️ View existing reports to avoid duplicates
- 🔔 Join a report to receive updates from rescuers
- 🔒 Anonymous reporting supported

---

## 🚀 Getting Started

### Installation (for local testing)

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
streamlit run kangalert.py

